		"name": "Tripitaka MCP Server API",
		"description": "Postman collection for testing the Tripitaka MCP Server in SSE mode.\n\n### How to use:\n1. Run the server in SSE mode:\n   ```bash\n   MCP_TRANSPORT=sse python main.py\n   ```\n2. The server will start on `http://localhost:8000` by default.\n3. Import this collection into Postman.\n4. First, call **Initialize** to start the session.\n5. Then you can call any of the **Tools**.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Connection",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Connect SSE",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/sse",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"sse"
							]
						},
						"description": "Establish SSE connection. In Postman, you can use the 'Events' tab or just call this to see if the server is up."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Initialize",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": \"1\",\n    \"method\": \"initialize\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"protocolVersion\": \"2024-11-05\",\n        \"capabilities\": {},\n        \"clientInfo\": {\n            \"name\": \"Postman-Client\",\n            \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n        }\n    }\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/messages",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"messages"
							]
